│ stop({"edit_points": [15340, 15342, "llvm/lib/Analysis/ScalarEvolution.cpp", "thoughts\": \"1. Understanding the Issue: The crash occurs due to infinite         │
│ recursion in the LoopGuards::collectFromPHI function when processing a PHI node with cyclic dependencies. The PHI node %2 depends on %3, and %3 (add i32 %2, 1)  │
│ depends back on %2, creating a cycle that causes endless recursive calls between getSCEV, createSCEV, and loop guard collection functions.\n\n2. Analyzing       │
│ `opt`'s Log: The log shows that ScalarEvolution is attempting to classify the PHI expression `{0,+,1}<nuw><nsw><%bb1>`, which indicates it recognizes this as an │
│ add recurrence. However, the loop guard collection mechanism is being invoked during SCEV computation, leading to the infinite recursion observed in the stack   │
│ trace.\n\n3. Root Cause Analysis: The LoopGuards::collectFromPHI function lacks protection against infinite recursion when processing PHI nodes that have cyclic │
│ dependencies. While it uses VisitedBlocks to prevent revisiting the same basic block, it doesn't prevent the SCEV computation from creating value-level cycles.  │
│ When SE.getSCEV(Phi.getIncomingValue(IncomingIdx)) is called on line 15356 for an incoming value that depends on the PHI itself, it triggers another round of    │
│ SCEV computation that eventually calls collectFromPHI again, creating infinite recursion.\n\n4. Proposed Edit Point(s): Add a recursion depth limit check at the │
│ beginning of collectFromPHI to prevent excessive recursion. The function already has a Depth parameter that is incremented when making recursive calls, but it's │
│ not being used to limit recursion. Adding a reasonable depth limit (e.g., 32) will prevent infinite recursion while still allowing legitimate deep               │
│ analyses.\n\n5. Conclusion: This fix prevents the infinite recursion crash by limiting the depth of recursive calls in the loop guard collection logic. It       │
│ maintains the correctness of the analysis for normal cases while protecting against pathological inputs with cyclic PHI dependencies."]})                        │
