│                                                                                                                                                                  │
│ ### Root Cause Analysis ###                                                                                                                                      │
│                                                                                                                                                                  │
│ -------------------- BEGIN --------------------                                                                                                                  │
│ 1. Understanding the Issue: The crash occurs due to infinite recursion in the LoopGuards::collectFromPHI function when processing a PHI node with cyclic         │
│ dependencies. The PHI node %2 depends on %3, and %3 (add i32 %2, 1) depends back on %2, creating a cycle that causes endless recursive calls between getSCEV,    │
│ createSCEV, and loop guard collection functions.                                                                                                                 │
│                                                                                                                                                                  │
│ 2. Analyzing `opt`'s Log: The log shows that ScalarEvolution is attempting to classify the PHI expression `{0,+,1}<nuw><nsw><%bb1>`, which indicates it          │
│ recognizes this as an add recurrence. However, the loop guard collection mechanism is being invoked during SCEV computation, leading to the infinite recursion   │
│ observed in the stack trace.                                                                                                                                     │
│                                                                                                                                                                  │
